or create an iso file on android storage,
dd bs=1048576 count=512 if=/dev/zero of=/sdcard/swap.iso
mknod /dev/block/loop8 b 7 8
mkswap /sdcard/swap.iso
losetup /dev/block/loop8 /sdcard/swap.iso
mkswap /dev/block/loop8
swapon /dev/block/loop8
free -h

it's weird, android swapon can work on /mnt/media_rw/xxx/swap.iso
but cp that swap.iso to /sdcard/script/, swapon it will error invalid parameter
the success one is exfat file system, fail on is fat32

if there is 2GB disk space partition on android, and it's /dev/block/mmcblk1p5
then 
mkswap /dev/block/mmcblk1p5
swapon /dev/block/mmcblk1p5
sysctl -w vm.swappiness=50 

-----------------------------
on PC
umask 066
mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt
sudo dd bs=1M count=2046 if=/dev/zero of=/mnt/swap.iso
sudo mkswap /mnt/swap.iso
sudo umount /mnt 

on android-x86
ls /mnt/media_rw/ # find out where usb-stick is mounted
swapon /mnt/media_rw/xxx/swap.iso
free -h

cube i6 air, the card reader is very slow, and the emmc storage is slow too,
usb 3.0 stick connected via otg, faster than card reader and emmc
the usb stick no need to be ext4, exfat or vfat will ok, since swap on an iso file,
not a partition

